028 Execution Contexts and the Execution Statck.mp4

//Execution Context:
A box, a container, or a wrapper which stores variables and in 
which a piece of our code is evaluated and executed.

//The default: Global Execution Context
- Code that is not inside any function
- Associated with the global object
- In the browser, that is the window object.
  ie. 
  lastName === window.lastName;   //returns true

